4:
Man, this is awkward... Kugui's super
bothered by what happened
yesterday.
7:
At the very least, she demonstrated
that her sense of control is
improving... Though I'm sure that's
little comfort at the moment.
16:
Your power's amazing! That yokai
looked and acted like the real deal!
24:
Why would I be? It's not every day I
get to see something THAT cool!
33:
...Don't tell me you were quiet this
whole time because you weren't
sure how to start the conversation.
36:
Hey, I was trying not to be awkward!
I wanted to tell her yesterday, but
she zoomed away before I could get
the chance.
44: No? I've got no reason to be!
48: Thank goodness... I was so worried!
54:
But yeah, I really wanna see more of
your actual artâ€”no holding back!
58:
It's too dangerous... You saw what
happened yesterday.
62: High risk, high reward? Pretty please?
68:
I also believe you should give it
another attempt.
71:
Even though it was only for a
moment, that yokai listened to you.
The potential is there.
73:
Time is of the essence too. You only
have 5 days left before you have to
present your entry for the festival.
79:
But there's... There's no telling what
could happen! Last time was
already unusual enough.
83:
Hmm... What if it wasn't a REAL yokai
that you were working with? Like...
How about a made-up one instead?
88:
Theoretically, I can animate
anything I create...
93:
Then let's have you try painting one
of my old works!
98: Thanks for waiting! Here it is!
106:
Similar, but not quite. It's only got
one head... Some type of dragon
yokai, I imagine?
110:
Yep, that's right! When I was a kid, I
used to make up all sorts of yokai
and daydream about them.
112:
I painted this one from memory. It's
my best work yet!
115:
Huh, so it's a completely fake yokai...
One that looks pretty real.
128:
It's my painting, isn't it? You can tell
me, I won't be offended.
133:
I recognize the dragon, even though
there's no way I could have seen it
before today...
136:
Whoa, seriously? But I drew it, like, a
month ago!
139: I'm just as confused as you are...
144:
Okay, maybe we shouldn't do this
after all! Are you okay?
147: Yes... I'm fine. Let us continue.
150:
I'm so close to remembering... I must
paint.
155:
My mind doesn't recall, but my body
does.
157:
Bone, flesh, scales... My hands move
on their own.
160:
Have I painted this very same
creature before?
168:
Everyone's running away... Don't
leave me...
171: I don't want to be alone!
177: I... remember! This dragon was... my...
195:
Suizen! How... Were you watching us
this whole time?!
198:
I had a shikigami follow you around,
just in case... I had hoped it wouldn't
come to this.
201:
This isn't your average beast! Be on
your guard!
